# Avoid useEffect by default

- Do not introduce `useEffect` in new code unless the user explicitly asks for it.
- Prefer direct event-driven logic with `useCallback` and explicit function calls.
- For mount-time element setup, use callback refs (`ref={(node) => { ... }}`) or a stable callback + ref guard instead of `useEffect`.
- Keep side effects close to the triggering action (handlers, async actions, mutation callbacks) instead of lifecycle effects.
- If existing code uses `useEffect`, do not refactor it unless the current task requires touching that behavior.

## Preferred patterns

```tsx
// Mount/setup without useEffect
const initializedRef = useRef(false)
const onContainerRef = useCallback((node: HTMLDivElement | null) => {
  if (!node || initializedRef.current) return
  initializedRef.current = true
  setupMap(node)
}, [setupMap])
```

```tsx
// Action-driven updates
const handleSave = useCallback(async () => {
  await saveTask(formState)
  toast.success('Saved')
}, [formState, saveTask])
```
